title: Germination Data
description:
Description
“A 2 x 2 factorial experiment comparing 2 types of seed and 2 root extracts. There are 5 or 6 replicates in each 
of the 4 treatment groups, and each replicate comprises a number of seeds varying between 4 and 81. The response 
variable is the proportion of seeds germinating in each replicate.” (Crowder, 1978, Table 3).

parameters.seed: a factor with 2 levels: O73 and O75.
parameters.root: a factor with 2 levels BEAN and CUCUMBER.
parameters.y: a numeric vector: the number of seeds which actually germinated.
parameters.n: a numeric vector: the number of seeds exposed to germination.

format: A data frame with 21 observations on the following 4 variables.
